definition.value: This is an AE which is a collection of pus in the pleural cavity caused by microorganisms, usually bacteria.
This is an AE which is a rare and potentially limb- and life-threatening injury, that results from high-energy trauma.
This is an AE which is an acute exacerbation of asthma that does not respond to standard treatments of bronchodilators (inhalers) and corticosteroids.
This is an AE which is a long-term inflammatory disease of the airways of the lungs and is crisis.
This is an AE which occurs when breathing is impeded by a constricted or obstructed throat or windpipe.
This is an AE which is a feeling of deficient supply of oxygen to the body that arises from abnormal breathing.
This is an AE which is a blockage of respiration in the airway that hinders the free flow of air and is reversible.
This is an AE which is the vibration of respiratory structures and the resulting sound due to obstructed air movement during breathing while sleeping.
This is an AE which is a type of respiratory infection that is usually caused by a virus.

This is an AE which is a chronic, inflammatory skin disease of unknown cause which can affect any body part of any person but has a strong preference for the genitals (penis, vulva) and is also known as balanitis xerotica obliterans (BXO) when it affects the penis.
This is an AE which is the most common demyelinating disease, in which the insulating covers of nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord are damaged and it has plaque.
This is an AE which is a neuropathological condition with severe neuronal cell loss and gliosis in the hippocampus, specifically in the CA-1 (Cornu Ammonis area 1) and subiculum of the hippocampus.
This is an AE which is a form of Hodgkin's lymphoma that is the most common subtype of HL in developed countries.
This is an AE which is a genetic multisystem disorder characterised by widespread hamartomas in several organs, including the brain, heart, skin, eyes, kidney, lung, and liver.
This is an AE which refers epidermal thickening characterized by visible and palpable thickening of the skin with accentuated skin markings.
This is an AE which is a disease in which the white matter of the brain appears damaged in concentric layers, leaving the axis cylinder intact.
This is an AE which is dermal thickening causing the cutaneous surface to feel thicker and firmer.
This ia an AE which is a  eyelid skin condition characterized by excessively dry skin.
This is an AE which pressure is placed on the skin, the skin is damaged and is unable to be repaired due to the lack of blood perfusing the tissue.
This is an AE which is the condition of dissimilar particles or surfaces to cling to one another  on the skin.
This is an AE which is a skin condition present at birth regardless of its cause.
This is an AE which is a small elevation of the skin containing cloudy or purulent material (pus) usually consisting of necrotic inflammatory cells.
This is an AE which is an enlargement of skin tissue caused by an increase in the amount of organic tissue that results from cell proliferation.
This is an AE which is the degeneration of skin tissue, due to disease or malnutrition, most likely due to heredity.
This is an Ae which is the increase in the volume of skin tissue due to the enlargement of its component cells.
This is an AE which is the result of a continuous process based on degenerative skin cell changes, affecting tissues or organs, which will increasingly deteriorate over time.
This is an AE which is underdevelopment or incomplete development of a skin tissue .
This is an AE which is a mass of cells that lacks the ability to either invade neighboring tissue or metastasize and occurs on the skin.

This is an AE which is a small cutaneous depressions that can be noted on any part of the body and may be caused by traumatic, mechanical, metabolic, and genetic factors as well as by exposure to infections or drugs.
This is an AE which may present as either a superficial or deep infection of the skin, hair, and/or nails.

label.value: graft versus host disease in skin AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is the most frequent and potentially fatal complication of an allogeneic hematopoietic progenitor cell transplantation  on the skin.

This is an AE which is a heterogeneous group of diseases, characterized by a skin inflammatory reaction triggered by a wide variety of stimuli, including infections, foreign bodies, malignancy, metabolites, and chemicals.
This is an AE which is a usually benign vascular skin tumor derived from blood vessel cell types.
This is an AE which is a sore on the skin or a mucous membrane, accompanied by the disintegration of tissue.
This is an AE which is a type of abnormal and excessive growth of skin tissue .

label.value: neuroendocrine carcinoma of the skin AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is skin neoplasms that arise from  cells of the endocrine  and nervous systems  .
This is an AE which refers to skin lesions with a degree of risk of progression to squamous cell carcinoma.

This is an AE which is most commonly caused by infection by the bacterium Staphylococcus aureus, resulting in a painful swollen area on the skin caused by an accumulation of pus and dead tissue，meantime it often recurs.
This is an AE which is a skin condition in which skin is prone to itching and irritation experienced as a subjective sensation when using cosmetics and toiletries.
This is an  AE which bacterial skin infections include Cellulitis, Erysipelas,Folliculitis and Impetigo.
